  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to 275°F (135°C).",
    "Season the pork back ribs with smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper. ",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, and honey. ",
    "Brush the yogurt mixture onto the ribs. ",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together chopped fresh dill and garlic powder. ",
    "Sprinkle the dill mixture over the ribs. ",
    "Grill the ribs for 2 hours, or until they are tender and caramelized. ",
    "Meanwhile, grill the pickle and cucumber slices until they are lightly charred. ",
    "Brush the ribs with olive oil during the last 10 minutes of grilling. ",
    "Once the ribs are done, let them rest for 5 minutes before slicing. ",
    "Serve the ribs with the grilled pickles and cucumber slices. "
  ],
